review_blob: Pours with a full bodied caramel head to match its caramel brown appearance. Thick appearance which shows its unfilteredness. Doesnt really look like an ipa. Upon first taste you definitely get the toasty malt. Its smooth but bitter on the tongue as the hops hit you hard. They also stay with you deep in the palate. This isnt your typical ipa and not a favorite but its very drinkable.

A very refreshing citrusy aroma that is orange in color and very pleasant to the nose. An orange wheat in taste and is also very pleasant on the palate. Overall its a very drinkable summer ale which is definately a beer that you can have many on a hot day.

Very pleasant aroma w/hints of Coffee. A sweet coffee taste w/the Bourbon overtones. Very good on the palate leaving a mix of the coffee and bourbon but not boozy at all. Overall its as good as advertised if not better. 2014 version.

Light tartness aroma. Very pale in appearance and pours with a light head. Very light bodied with a tart taste. An easy drinking ale that is light on the palate and is drinkable. It sort of reminds me of drinking a High Life.
A very good oktoberfest beer. Not the best but very good. Probably my favorite abc beer.
One of my favorites. perfect look and taste. An imperial ipa that I could drink all day.
